SIMPLE: opportunistic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: opportunistic
<hw>opportunistic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>taking immediate
advantage, often unethically, of any circumstance of possible benefit;
practising opportunism.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> opportunist, timeserving.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Causing disease only when the
immune system of the host has been weakened, or other damage to the host
provides special opportunity for invasion; -- of microorganisms or
infectious diseases; <as>as, <ex>opportunistic</ex> pathogens may infect
a burn site; AIDS predisposes a patient to <ex>opportunistic</ex>
infection</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opportunity</ent>⟦br⟧
